From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Thu, 6 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add a build ID to libghostty-vt

Fedora's RPM debuginfo extraction requires a build ID note on shared
libraries. Without it, the COPR build fails during `%install` when
`find-debuginfo` scans `libghostty-vt.so`.
---
 src/build/GhosttyLibVt.zig | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/build/GhosttyLibVt.zig b/src/build/GhosttyLibVt.zig
index 1716e5d..7253fb1 100644
--- a/src/build/GhosttyLibVt.zig
+++ b/src/build/GhosttyLibVt.zig
@@ -48,6 +48,9 @@ pub fn initShared(
         .root_module = zig.vt_c,
         .version = std.SemanticVersion{ .major = 0, .minor = 1, .patch = 0 },
     });
+    // Fedora RPM debuginfo extraction requires a build ID on shared libraries.
+    // Zig defaults to omitting it because it makes linking a bit slower.
+    lib.build_id = .fast;
     lib.installHeadersDirectory(
         b.path("include/ghostty"),
         "ghostty",
-- 
